        <main class="docs-content">
            <h1>User <span class="accent">Guide</span></h1>
            <p>Learn how to use GemCrest's features to manage your jewelry business efficiently.</p>

            <h2>Dashboard Overview</h2>
            <p>The dashboard provides an at-a-glance view of your business:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Today's Sales:</strong> Total revenue for the current day</li>
                <li><strong>Invoice Count:</strong> Number of invoices created today</li>
                <li><strong>Recent Invoices:</strong> Quick access to recent transactions</li>
                <li><strong>Metal Rates:</strong> Current gold and silver prices</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Creating an Invoice</h2>
            <p>To create a new invoice:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Click <strong>"New Invoice"</strong> in the sidebar</li>
                <li>Select or add a customer</li>
                <li>Add items to the invoice (see below)</li>
                <li>Review totals and apply discounts if needed</li>
                <li>Save and print the invoice</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Adding Billing Items</h3>
            <p>For each item sold:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Enter item description (e.g., "Gold Chain", "Diamond Ring")</li>
                <li>Specify gross weight and net weight</li>
                <li>Select metal type and purity (22K, 18K, etc.)</li>
                <li>Enter making charges (percentage or flat rate)</li>
                <li>The system calculates the price automatically</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Old Gold Exchange</h3>
            <p>To accept old jewelry as payment:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>In the Exchange section, click "Add Exchange Item"</li>
                <li>Enter the weight and purity of the old jewelry</li>
                <li>The exchange value is deducted from the total</li>
            </ol>

            <h2>Inventory Management</h2>
            <p>Track your stock in real-time:</p>

            <h3>Adding Products</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Go to <strong>Inventory → Add Product</strong></li>
                <li>Enter product details: name, category, weight, purity</li>
                <li>Add HUID if applicable</li>
                <li>Set initial stock quantity</li>
                <li>Save the product</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Stock Updates</h3>
            <p>Stock is automatically updated when you create invoices. For manual adjustments:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Go to <strong>Inventory</strong></li>
                <li>Find the product and click "Edit"</li>
                <li>Adjust the stock quantity</li>
                <li>Save changes</li>
            </ol>

            <h2>Customer Management</h2>
            <p>Maintain detailed customer records:</p>

            <h3>Adding Customers</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Go to <strong>Customers → Add New</strong></li>
                <li>Enter name, phone, and email</li>
                <li>Enter pincode — city and state auto-fill</li>
                <li>Add any notes or preferences</li>
                <li>Save the customer</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Customer History</h3>
            <p>View a customer's complete purchase history by clicking on their profile. This helps with personalized
                service and follow-ups.</p>

            <h2>Metal Rates</h2>
            <p>Keep your pricing accurate by updating metal rates daily:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Go to <strong>Metal Rates</strong></li>
                <li>Enter today's 24K gold rate per gram</li>
                <li>Enter fine silver rate per gram</li>
                <li>Other purity rates are calculated automatically</li>
            </ol>

            <div class="callout callout-tip">
                <strong>Tip:</strong> Update metal rates first thing each morning before creating invoices.
            </div>

            <h2>Printing Invoices</h2>
            <p>GemCrest supports multiple print formats:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Standard A4:</strong> Full-page professional invoices</li>
                <li><strong>Thermal:</strong> For POS thermal printers</li>
                <li><strong>Custom Templates:</strong> Configure in Settings</li>
            </ul>
